s en dalen, terwijl het zuiden van Isra&euml;l is vooral woestijn, echter door innovatieve bewatering technieken wordt ook de Negev woestijn geleidelijk steeds meer veranderd in grond met een agrarische toepassing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"font-size: 30px; width: 740px; margin-left: 38px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"> Zoekwoorden</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 38px; width: 740px;\">Kosher Kosjer koosjer koosjere wijn rood wit rode ros&eacute; droge witte droog zoet droge zoete sweet dry white Israel Israelische Avondmaal Avondmaalwijn Sacramental King David Israel Carmel Winery trocken Wein Rot Weiss Wei&szlig;wein glatt Kasjroet Pesach Rabbijn rabbinical supervision posek hechsher kashrut yayin kash&eacute;r Sabbath Sabbat Shalom mevushal kosher for Passover winemaking process  harvesting of the grapes fermentation Jewish diaspora  mashgichim sacramental wine tannins flavors Jewish holidays Passover Seder grape juice Redemption of First-born Borei Pri HaGafen Ein Simcha Ela BeBasar Veyayin nichnas yayin yatza sod Torah Maimonides Code of Jewish Law Mashgiach Shatnez Bishul israel Cholov Yisroel Pas Yisroel Orlah prohibition Badatz BC Kosher Central Rabbinical Congress Council COR Kashruth Council of Canada Kosher Supervision of America London Beth Din OK Kosher Certification Orthodox Union Rabbinical Council Tav HaYosher Alcoholic beverages Kiddush Joodse feestdagen Ashkenazi halakhic synagoge Hasidic and     Israeli  vineyard   Yatir    Upper Galilee   Lower Galilee   Jezreel Valley   Emek Hefer  Golan  Jerusalem Jeruzalem      Kosher for Pesach   Rosh Hashanah   Shabbat  Holyday   supervising   Mehadrin very kosher   Kasher Badatz   Chareidis  Sephardic   Ashkenazic Asjkenazische Sefardische   jews    cooked  boiled Pasteurized     rabbinate  rabbi  fragrance  taste smaak    barrel wood  oak  fruit     Kiddush wine Kidoesh wijn toast    fortified wine    bewaar bewaren    dessert wijn   sweet wine   wine boutique  Merlot  Shiraz  Zinfandel grape druif   